---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="About — Cristian Dubineanschi"
  description="Interdisciplinary artist and visual designer in Cluj-Napoca, working with digital systems, interactive media, and design."
>
  <div class="about-container container" id="about-main-container">
    <!-- Page Header -->
    <section class="about-header" id="about-title-sec">
      <div class="header-line" id="about-line-div"></div>
      <span class="system-code">Interdisciplinary artist — Cluj-Napoca, RO · Chișinău, MD</span>
      <h1 class="page-title cursor" id="about-page-title">About</h1>
    </section>

    <!-- Two Column Data Grid -->
    <div class="about-grid" id="about-grid-content">
      <!-- Left Column: Biography & System Concept -->
      <div class="about-left" id="about-bio-column">
        <h2 class="section-title">01. Practice</h2>
        <div class="bio-text">
          <p>
            I'm an interdisciplinary artist and visual designer based in Cluj-Napoca, Romania,
            originally from Chișinău, Moldova. I work with the parts of digital life most people
            never see, like platforms, algorithms, and the data moving underneath them, and I turn
            them into things you can look at and interact with.
          </p>
          <p>
            I came to installation the long way round. I started out in photography and video,
            worked on organising festivals, contributed static installations, and ran live VJ
            projections at events across Cluj-Napoca and Chișinău. Over the last couple of years I
            moved toward interactive work, which is what pushed me into the Master's in Digital
            Interactive Arts.
          </p>
          <p>
            I don't think of a medium as a fixed category. My process is rooted in play and inquiry:
            I experiment with new tools and raw data and let the form surface on its own. I look for
            sense in the abstract and complexity in the simple. The question I keep coming back to:
            how do these systems shape what we do, what we notice, and what we think is possible?
            For me design isn't only a way to explain something. It can also make an argument.
          </p>
          <p>
            Right now I'm doing a Master's in Digital Interactive Arts at Babeș-Bolyai University,
            in the Faculty of Theatre and Film, where most of my work is collective and
            cross-disciplinary. I keep circling one tension: when a digital experience should be
            clear, and when it's better off staying ambiguous.
          </p>
        </div>

        <p class="bio-cta">
          If any of this resonates, I'd like to hear from you, whether that's working on something
          together, a commission, showing the work, or just a conversation.
          <a href="/contact">Get in touch →</a>
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Right Column: System Specs & History Log -->
      <div class="about-right" id="about-log-column">
        <!-- Core Hardware Stack -->
        <section class="hardware-stack-section">
          <h2 class="section-title">02. Tools & technologies</h2>
          <div class="hardware-grid">
            <div class="hw-block">
              <span class="hw-title">DESIGN & MEDIA</span>
              <ul class="hw-list">
                <li>Figma, Webflow, InVision (Prototyping)</li>
                <li>TouchDesigner, Max/MSP, Ableton Live</li>
                <li>Blender (3D Modeling & Workflows)</li>
                <li>Adobe Creative Cloud (Premiere, After Effects, DTP)</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="hw-block">
              <span class="hw-title">SENSING & HARDWARE</span>
              <ul class="hw-list">
                <li>Microsoft Kinect (Gesture Mapping & Point Clouds)</li>
                <li>Addressable LED controllers & microcontrollers (ESP32, WLED, Arduino)</li>
                <li>Augmented Reality (AR) development frameworks</li>
                <li>Digital projection & Cinema projection networks</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Exhibitions & selected projects (artist CV) -->
        <section class="exhibitions-section">
          <h2 class="section-title">03. Exhibitions & selected projects</h2>
          <div class="log-timeline">
            <div class="log-item">
              <div class="log-meta">
                <span class="log-date">[2026]</span>
                <span class="log-loc">Cluj-Napoca, RO</span>
              </div>
              <div class="log-details">
                <span class="log-project">(in)between.wav — Exhibited</span>
                <p class="log-desc">
                  Interactive light installation. Exhibited at the Ethnographical Museum of
                  Transylvania. Master of Digital Interactive Arts (UBB), coordinated by Prof.
                  Cristina Pop-Tiron.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="log-item">
              <div class="log-meta">
                <span class="log-date">[2026]</span>
                <span class="log-loc">Cluj-Napoca, RO</span>
              </div>
              <div class="log-details">
                <span class="log-project">IcarusSyn .01 — In production</span>
                <p class="log-desc">
                  Interactive generative LED sphere, developed thanks to a UBB cultural-artistic
                  scholarship awarded to produce it. In production toward a public exhibition.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="log-item">
              <div class="log-meta">
                <span class="log-date">[2025]</span>
                <span class="log-loc">Cluj-Napoca, RO</span>
              </div>
              <div class="log-details">
                <span class="log-project">Oracolul2000 — Collaboration</span>
                <p class="log-desc">
                  Environmental LED installation for a project signed by Călin Nahaiciuc, shown in a
                  gallery space in Cluj-Napoca.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="log-item">
              <div class="log-meta">
                <span class="log-date">[2025]</span>
                <span class="log-loc">Cluj-Napoca, RO</span>
              </div>
              <div class="log-details">
                <span class="log-project">AR Installation — Reactor</span>
                <p class="log-desc">
                  Co-created an Augmented Reality installation at Reactor de Creație și Experiment,
                  exploring participative experiences in urban public space.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="log-item">
              <div class="log-meta">
                <span class="log-date">[2025]</span>
                <span class="log-loc">UBB FTF</span>
              </div>
              <div class="log-details">
                <span class="log-project">Rooted Structures / Bio-Sonic Dust</span>
                <p class="log-desc">
                  Interactive performance and audio-visual experiments developed within the Master
                  of Digital Interactive Arts (UBB).
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="log-item">
              <div class="log-meta">
                <span class="log-date">[2014 — present]</span>
                <span class="log-loc">Cluj-Napoca · Chișinău</span>
              </div>
              <div class="log-details">
                <span class="log-project">Earlier practice</span>
                <p class="log-desc">
                  Photography and video, static installations and live VJ projections at festivals
                  and events, across Cluj-Napoca and Chișinău.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Experience & education -->
        <section class="exhibitions-section">
          <h2 class="section-title">04. Experience & education</h2>
          <div class="log-timeline">
            <div class="log-item">
              <div class="log-meta">
                <span class="log-date">[2025.10]</span>
                <span class="log-loc">Cluj-Napoca, RO</span>
              </div>
              <div class="log-details">
                <span class="log-project">AR INSTALLATION CO-CREATOR</span>
                <p class="log-desc">
                  Reactor de Creație și Experiment. Developed an Augmented Reality installation
                  exploring participative experiences in urban public spaces.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="log-item">
              <div class="log-meta">
                <span class="log-date">[2025.09 - PRESENT]</span>
                <span class="log-loc">UBB FTF</span>
              </div>
              <div class="log-details">
                <span class="log-project">MASTER IN DIGITAL INTERACTIVE ARTS</span>
                <p class="log-desc">
                  Pursuing advanced studies in interactive systems, media installations, and
                  technological art frameworks.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="log-item">
              <div class="log-meta">
                <span class="log-date">[2025.09 - 2025.12]</span>
                <span class="log-loc">Dynares AI</span>
              </div>
              <div class="log-details">
                <span class="log-project">BRAND & VISUAL DESIGNER</span>
                <p class="log-desc">
                  Defined brand identity, visual direction, and web platform implementation for an
                  AI platform.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="log-item">
              <div class="log-meta">
                <span class="log-date">[2025.03 - 2025.08]</span>
                <span class="log-loc">TOKERO Exchange</span>
              </div>
              <div class="log-details">
                <span class="log-project">VISUAL DESIGNER & MARKETING</span>
                <p class="log-desc">
                  Created digital branding materials, lead magnets, and campaign visual identity
                  pipelines.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="log-item">
              <div class="log-meta">
                <span class="log-date">[2022.11 - PRESENT]</span>
                <span class="log-loc">Remote</span>
              </div>
              <div class="log-details">
                <span class="log-project">FREELANCE DESIGNER & MEDIA CREATOR</span>
                <p class="log-desc">
                  Deliver visual identity systems, interface design (UI/UX), video production, and
                  custom digital media solutions.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="log-item">
              <div class="log-meta">
                <span class="log-date">[2019.11 - 2023.09]</span>
                <span class="log-loc">Endava</span>
              </div>
              <div class="log-details">
                <span class="log-project">VISUAL DESIGNER</span>
                <p class="log-desc">
                  Designed visual communication systems, layout templates, and collaborative
                  workspaces (Figma/Miro).
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="log-item">
              <div class="log-meta">
                <span class="log-date">[2018.11 - 2019.11]</span>
                <span class="log-loc">Cluj-Napoca, RO</span>
              </div>
              <div class="log-details">
                <span class="log-project">PROJECTIONIST (PART-TIME)</span>
                <p class="log-desc">
                  Cinema Victoria. Operated digital projection systems and managed cinema content
                  networks.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="log-item">
              <div class="log-meta">
                <span class="log-date">[2017.10 - 2024.07]</span>
                <span class="log-loc">UBB FSPAC</span>
              </div>
              <div class="log-details">
                <span class="log-project">B.A. IN DIGITAL MEDIA</span>
                <p class="log-desc">
                  Graduated with Thesis: "The Importance of UI and UX Design in Mobile Banking
                  Applications – Case Study: BT Pay and ING Home'Bank".
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .about-container {
    padding-top: 3rem;
    padding-bottom: 5rem;
  }

  /* Page Header */
  .about-header {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }
  .header-line {
    height: 2px;
    background: linear-gradient(to right, var(--color-accent), transparent);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .system-code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.76rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  }
  .page-title {
    font-size: clamp(1.9rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    line-height: 1;
    text-transform: none;
  }

  /* Layout Grid */
  .about-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.1fr 1.3fr;
    gap: 4rem;
  }

  .section-title {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--color-text);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    padding-bottom: 0.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  /* Left Column details */
  .bio-text p {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .bio-cta {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }
  .bio-cta a {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-weight: 600;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .bio-cta a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .subsection-title {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  .technical-parameters {
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    background-color: var(--color-card-bg);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .param-row {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    padding: 0.75rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }
  .param-row:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
    padding-bottom: 0;
  }
  .param-name {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .param-val {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
    text-align: right;
  }

  /* Right Column details */
  .hardware-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }
  .hw-block {
    background: var(--color-card-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    padding: 1.25rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }
  .hw-title {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.76rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
  }
  .hw-list {
    list-style: none;
  }
  .hw-list li {
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 14px;
  }
  .hw-list li::before {
    content: "↳";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    opacity: 0.7;
  }

  .exhibitions-section + .exhibitions-section {
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }

  /* Archival log / Timeline */
  .log-timeline {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }
  .log-item {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 140px 1fr;
    gap: 1rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    padding-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .log-item:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
    padding-bottom: 0;
  }
  .log-meta {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 4px;
  }
  .log-date {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-weight: 700;
  }
  .log-loc {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    color: var(--color-muted);
  }
  .log-project {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  .log-desc {
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--color-muted);
  }

  /* Responsive Design */
  @media (max-width: 1024px) {
    .about-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 3rem;
    }
  }
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .about-container {
      padding-top: 1.5rem;
    }
    .log-item {
      grid-template-columns: 100px 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
